   1. NO PUBLIC-FACING DEPLOYMENT

      You MAY NOT deploy Breatic itself, or a substantially similar
      platform derived from Breatic, such that it is accessible to
      users outside the operator's organization over a public network --
      whether paid or free of charge.

      This restriction applies regardless of monetization model,
      including but not limited to: paid subscriptions, per-use fees,
      advertising, data collection in exchange for access, lead
      generation, or any other direct or indirect benefit derived from
      public access to Breatic.

      Permitted uses (not restricted by this clause):

        a. Internal deployment within a single organization -- including
           multi-workspace or multi-user setups for that organization's
           employees, members, or contractors.

        b. Self-hosting for individual or private-group use -- personal
           instances, or instances shared within a private community
           (e.g., a household, study group, or invite-only team) that is
           not publicly advertised or open to general sign-up.

        c. Building, deploying, or selling applications, content, or
           services produced with Breatic -- as opposed to offering
           Breatic itself as the service.

      "Organization" interpretation. For the purposes of this clause,
      "a single organization" includes a legal entity and its
      wholly-owned subsidiaries and affiliates, as interpreted in good
      faith. The Producer reserves the right to challenge
      interpretations that, in its reasonable judgment, are structured
      to evade this clause (for example: shell companies, or nominally
      separate entities under common control, used to operate what is
      effectively a public-facing service).

      For licensing inquiries regarding public-facing deployment,
      contact: licensing@orime.ai


